{
  "texts": [
    "For part (iii), we have Z ∈ ■ i x iff ■ i x ∈ Z iff (by the definition of R i) for every Z ′ ∈ R i (Z), x ∈ Z ′, i.e., Z ′ ∈ x, which is equivalent to R i (Z) ⊆ x.Second, we show that P g ⊆ RO(S, ⊑), i.e., every X ∈ P g satisfies persistence and refinability, so A g is a possibility frame.",
    "By definition of P g, X = x for some x ∈ A.",
    "For persistence, if X ′ ⊑ X, so X ′ ⊇ X, and X ∈ x, so x ∈ X, then x ∈ X ′ and hence X ′ ∈ x.",
    "For refinability, if X ̸ ∈ x, so x ̸ ∈ X, then X ′ = [X ∪ {-x}) is a proper filter, and X ′ ⊇ X, so X ′ ⊑ X.",
    "Moreover, for every proper filter X ′′ ⊑ X ′, i.e., X ′′ ⊇ X ′, we have x ̸ ∈ X ′′, so X ′′ ̸ ∈ x."
  ]
}